The paper deals with the power of interactive proof systems with verifiers modeled by semi-quantum two-way finite automata, which is a topic related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and quantum computing (cs.QL). The paper also involves the study of languages that can be recognized by these proof systems, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of the expected running time of these proof systems, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
